The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Durgapur Aug. 18: An Asansol schoolteacher was arrested today for beating up a Class IV student who apparently failed to pay Rs 50 for Independence Day and Teachers Day celebrations. 

 Police said Xavier Michael, 48, a Hindi teacher of St Josephs Primary School, thrashed Sulak Sharma with a wooden ruler. He has been released on bail.

 Calcutta: A technical evaluator with a private bank, Gagandeep Singh Makkar, 36, has been held on charges of che- ating. He had cleared 11 house loan applications worth Rs 90 lakh without confirming if the properties existed.

 Calcutta: The food processing and horticulture minister opened Bengal Blooms. The first outlet of the flower boutique chain is at City Centre.




